<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFEFFBFFC9598EA6DAB7805" pageId="19" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFEFFBFFC9598EA6D617984" blockId="19.[831,1437,1198,1380]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFEFFBFFC9598EA6ABD79A7" bold="true" box="[831,944,1198,1222]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is characterized by few inflated chambers with smooth ornamentation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFEFFBFFC9598A96DAB7805" blockId="19.[831,1437,1198,1380]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFEFFBFFC9598A96D7C7864" bold="true" box="[831,1137,1261,1285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Upper Cretaceous white chalk of the Paris Basin by D’ORBIGNY (1840). It is recorded in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene zones of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
